4.2.2 The ‌⁠​​⁠​ Open Source Initiative

The Open Source Initiative (OSI) was founded in 1998 

unlicke FSF osi does not have its own set of license 

instead the OSI has a set of pricciples and adds license to that list if the meet those principles 

One type of Open Source license is the BSD Berkeley Software Distribution

 These licenses state that you may redistribute the source and binaries as long as you maintain copyright notices and don’t imply that the original creator endorses your version. In other words "do what you want with this software, just don’t say you wrote it."

 permissive free software licenses because they are permissive in how you can redistribute the software

 Free/Libre/Open Source Software (FLOSS).

